          <p>The MBTI test shows that I'm a Debater (ENTP-T), after a further reading of what a debater personality means, it shows that I'm an excellent brainstormer where a debater can analyse problems in every point of view and tackle the problem in every aspect. Debaters also are quick thinkers, knowledgeable, energetic and charismatic. On the other side, from the learning style test, it shows that I'm a "Tactile Learner" where i learn by touching, which means that I need to have a grasp of the item or object that I'm learning by doing, which means that I'm a type of autodidact, learning to do thing by actively doing it. Last but not least, the creativity test shows that my creativity percentage is 63.16% (average), with that I'm short of the persistence aspect which means that I'm not that type to force myself to improve something that I consider to be "enough" or "good". Compiling everything, all of this test information might be useful to a group by helping a team to brainstorm all problem-solving solutions for all of the current situation. I can also help the team to learn when they do not know or have no idea on how to start the task as I learn while I do while bringing the team with me and go through the task together as a team.</p> 
  <br><br>
      <h4>Ideal Job</h4>
          <p>This job is an IT Business Analyst job. It is a bridge that connects both IT world and the business world as business analyst helps business to implement technology to meet their needs and requirements and to tackle each and every possible problem in a cost-effective manner. A bachelors degree in Business Information Systems to know what and how should we do. Next, the skills needed for this job includes working in groups, communication skill, problem-solving skill and critical-thinking skills. </p>
          <p>Comparing my ideal job with others, John and Nicholas has the same ideal job which is software engineer, where there is very less similarity, but I will still be working in order to fix the business problems using their coding skills. Patrick's ideal job will have the most common elements compared tot he others where we both need to organize staff, but his concer will be mainly about the organization's inventory management system. With Kelvin's job, his job is all about security where the common elements are we both analyse the problem and propse possible solutions but my ideal job is mainly about business processes while Kelvin's job is about the cyber security. Lastly, Tonys's job is almost similar to John's and Nicholas' ideal job, but Tony's job is about building the software website and application. Tony's job can collaborate withe my ideal job when I propose a problem which needs a technological solution, we can brainstorm how the application or sftware will be or look like to overcome the problems and turn it to a technological solution.</p>
