          <H4>Personal Information</H4>
              <p>Hi there, My name is John Mikael Usaraga, but most people call me Mikey. My studentID is S3842470. I was born in Melbourne, Australia, however, my parents are both Filipino. At home, my parents communicate to me in Tagalog, but I can only understand what they are saying because I have trouble speaking it as English is my native language. I am currently studying the Bachelor of Information Technology at RMIT. My hobbies include playing video games, watching anime and playing sports such as badminton and basketball. I have been playing badminton for 5-6 years now, but I don't play it as frequently as I used to.</p>
              <p>Growing up I had always played video games on console and pc. When playing these games there would sometimes be a new patch/update to a game before it runs. What intrigued me was how these patches were able to improve the game whether it be to fix a bug or to add more content to the game. From this, I started to develop an interest in IT as I wanted to find out how these updates worked. Having researched about it I came to an understanding that IT is used in a lot more interesting ways and am now fascinated by the actual coding/programming behind certain programs/software.  </p>
