  <br><br>
          <h4>Ideal Job</h4>
              <p>My ideal job is working as a software engineer, developing and building computer systems software and applications software. This occupation appeals to me the most as the work I'd do could branch out into developing operating systems and computer games. Due to my experiences growing up, being influenced by video games, I believe that this job is ideal for me. For this job, I would need to master a variety of programming languages, such as C++, C#, JavaScript, and Python. Some general skills I would also need to have for this job include software development, Object-oriented design (OOD), Software testing and debugging, problem-solving and logical thinking, written and verbal communication, teamwork.</p>
              <p>Comparing this job with those of the other members of this group, I have come to realize how IT can expand into different types of jobs. Out of the 6 members of the group, I do share the same Job interest with one of them. What differentiates my ideal job with the rest, is that this job focuses on developing and building computer systems software and applications software, whereas the other ones focus on aspects such as: carrying out security measures to protect computer networks and systems, managing inventory tracking systems, designing software systems and applications, and analyzing how well software and hardware fit the business needs of their employer or a client. Although, as most of the jobs each group member finds ideal is different, they all do share a similarity when it comes to some of the requirements for the job and also some general skills to have.</p>    
