          <H4>Team Profile</H4>
              <p>The Myers Briggs test results show that I’m an Advocate (INFJ-T). Upon further inspection an Advocate has an introverted mind, intuitive energy, feeling nature, judging tactics and turbulent identity. An advocate is sensitive to how others feel, creative and focused on the future. I believe I have all of those traits except for the Intuitive nature, where I believe I am more observant and can pick things up. According to the Learning test I took, I’m a visual learner. As a visual learner I need graphs, pictures and to read reports to understand the content better. I need to be able to write down information to contain it. This test accurately represents how I learn. I usually study using pictures and notes that use colour or diagrams to study. My creativity test result is 55.01, this means I can manage with work given to me in quantities and manage it very well, showing how organised I am. My work can be anything and I will be able to accept the work, even if it's contradictory. My perspective also shows that I am able to shift my perspective depending on the situation, making me flexible. I believe this test is also accurate, I feel like I’m very organised being on top of everything I do and I’m able to complete multiple different tasks. The test also says that I can shift my perspective depending on the situation and I think that's true, there have been many accounts where I can adapt to the situation. I probably feel like I need a bit of apparent connection before I can understand it and that I have more persistence then what the test says I do. This information can be helpful to the group, letting them know I can make decisions, my organisation skills, how my learning style is visual and I’m flexible with the workload and my position in the group.</p>
