          <h4>Ideal Job</h4>
          <p>My ideal job is a Software Engineer. A Software Engineer creates an outline for programmers to program. They work closely with team members and internal participants to problem solve through software development. Software Engineers need strong database development skills, ability to communicate effectively and efficiently, strong problem-solving skills and ability to use web services. I have the same ideal job as Mikey except he prefers to be in a senior role which may require him to have more of a leadership role. Gerald’s ideal job is different to mine, as mine concerns code and software development while his is focused around using analysis and design techniques to fix business problems with information technology. Tony’s job is very similar to mine dealing with code, but mine develops what coders should do, he troubleshoots the coding problems and what processors and technologies the development team should use. Kelvin’s ideal job is focused on security for companies and doesn’t this by monitoring security issues and installs software to protect their systems, they may create the softwares that they use, which is linked to my job, but my job is focused on creating softwares and code. Partick and I’s job aren’t closely linked, but my job can create softwares that Patrick may implement when monitoring transactions, margins, returns, and other financial data to inform decision makers. <p>
            <ul>
            <li>5 years of IT industry experience, with a track record of quality on-time releases</li>
            <li>Strong database development skills</li>
            <li>Ability to communicate effectively and efficiently within and between teams</li>
            <li>Computer Science degree or related qualification</li>
            <li>Strong problem-solving skills</li>
            <li>Desired skills and knowledge</li>
            <li>Strong background on the Microsoft platforms</li>
            <li>Web services</li>
            </ul>
            <p>The skills I currently have are; 3 years of experience coding in Visual Basic, a year of experience coding in Python, little experience with App Inventor and Game Maker. </p>
