          <p>When comparing and contrasting each ideal job for each person in the group. It seems like although the common element behind most ideal jobs are IT related, each job is related to a different part of IT/combined with other areas. Out of our group my job is the most similar or at least shares similar traits as software engineering. As software engineering applies mathematical analysis and the principles of computer science in order to design and develop computer software where as a software architect is a developer who communicates with businesses and clients to design and execute solutions with a team of software engineers. So the commonality between these two jobs is that we use the knowledge of computer science to make or fix something. Whereas the other jobs are different in terms of the goal. For example cybersecurity is about the protection of computer networks and systems and a system analysis focuses on the analysis of information systems.  So some jobs may share similar aspects of the job.Even a job like  system and inventory analysis still uses IT to a certain degree to make it easier to keep track of inventory. Overall I think that our career plans across the group are quite different as each job goes over the different aspects of IT.</p>
