  <br><br><br>
  <h1>IT Work</h1>
        <h3>What kind of work is done by the IT professional?</h3>
          <p>The It professional works in ANZ as an application support analyst. Their team supports the foreign exchange applications operated by ANZ. Their team is responsible for ensuring that our FX (foreign exchange) applications are running efficiently for use by their FX traders</p>
<br><br>

        <h3>What kinds of people does the IT professional interact with? Are they other IT  professionals? Clients? Investors? The general public?</h3>
          <p>They mostly interact with other IT professionals within ANZ, mostly developers that have developed the application they currently support. They also deal with the FX traders that use their applications</p>
  <br><br>

        <h3>Where does the IT professional spend most of their time?</h3>
          <p></p>
<br><br>

        <h3>What aspect of their position is most challenging? </h3>
          <p>The most challenging aspect of their job is when they have system wide issues that prevent FX traders from using their applications. Every minute that their application is not running has financial impact on the business </p>
<br><br>
    
  
  
  <br><br><br>
  <h1>IT Technologies</h1>
  <ol>
    <li style="font-size:30px"><h2>Cloud Computing</h2></li>
        <h3>What does it do?</h3>
        <ol type="A">
          <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>What is the state of the art of this new technology?</h4></li>
            <p>Currently the state of the art for cloud computing is Kamatera, but have other top competitors like Amazon Web Services and Google Cloud. Kamatera is a cloud service that has “14 Global Data Centers across 4 continents” (15 Top Cloud Computing Service Provider Companies, 2020) making their cloud service very secure, and generates a lot of storage for users to create/use for work, school, or personal materials. The cloud computing service is very “customisable and tailored” (Top 21 Cloud Computing Service Provider Companies in 2020, 2020) for complete user control with ease of use, from the scalability to the ability to “add load balancers, firewalls, private networks and even apps” (Top 21 Cloud Computing Service Provider Companies in 2020, 2020). </p>
            <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>What can be done now?</h4></li>
            <p>Cloud computing already has a stable infrastructure, but one modification to it can be with AI. AI can be embedded with the cloud where AI “monitors, manages, and even self-heal when an issue occurs.” (Alton, 2020). AI is also able to make data management more efficient helping the way data is “ingested, updated, and managed” (Alton, 2020), these improvements will have a major impact on “marketing, customer service, and supply chain data management” (Alton, 2020). Cloud computing has security flaws, but it can be improved by implementing Multi-factor authentication. It is the “most efficient and cheapest way” (D'Silva, 2020) to secure data. Cloud computing can also benefit from WANOP or load-balancing, this controls the flow of traffic between distributed data center locations” (Kleyman, 2020) and load-balancing allows you to “scale your data center” (Kleyman, 2020). Data control is important for cloud storage, and it can be improved by implementing “data tiers” (Kleyman, 2020) which you can assign data to the right type of storage.</p>
            <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>What is likely to be done soon (say in the next 3 years)?</h4></li>
            <p>The transition to fully digital methods of storing and transmitting data is possible today due to the power of cloud services, in the future these will be able to be scaled up tremendously and aid in many different fields. A breakthrough was announced in 2019 by google in which a quantum computer they developed was able to solve a mathematical calculation that would take today's supercomputers 10,000 years to complete, in only three and a half minutes. This leads to the potential of handling more complex data. A remote surgery utilizing 5G and cloud services was done, a surgeon from a Chinese city of Sanya was able to operate on a patient in Beijing which is nearly 1,900 miles away. This potential may allow for even greater, more complex medical procedures to be undertaken by a specialist while not needing to be directly in contact with the patient.</p>
            <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>What technological or other developments make this possible?</h4></li>
            <p>The development of quicker internet quality and speed allow cloud services to provide what they offer with speed and reliability in today’s busy world. Improving the network speed makes consumers desire a quick and responsive service that allows for almost real time management of cloud services. The digital security that is needed to ensure that all data stored and distributed is safe and secure without it being lost, corrupted and tampered with. As the reliance of cloud backups and cloud services grow day by day the required space to store and hold all the information distributed grows, data storages and their ability to contain all the information is vital in ensuring that the service is able to sustain all its users and provide their selected usages.</p>
        </ol>

      <br><br>  

        <h3>What is the likely impact?</h3>
          <p>One of the impacts to an organization includes them having a lower operating cost, this is due to the elimination of the need to build the company’s own IT infrastructure, thus, saving land and capital in terms of factors of production (2014). In addition to that, companies may also reduce the need of expenditure in services and maintenance costs. On top of that, there will also be a change in the business environment where files and other documents can be accessible anywhere and anytime as long as the user is connected to the internet. The most affected sector in the organization is the user (staff), as they need to get used to the change in collaboration. Next, is the IT maintenance team, they will have a little less work in managing the files and documents in the organization, but the IT security team will be allocated more as they need to keep the business data and documents safe. The upper management can keep track on how their team is performing based on the contributions of the team and the amount of time spent reflected in the cloud service. Due to the concern about security threats, organizations may want to hire people to keep their files and documents safe in the cloud (2014) .There will be a cut in the IT maintenance sector where after the cloud computing is implemented in the organization and more allocation of manpower to the IT security team as the organization will need to secure their datas which is held by the third party organization (The cloud). There will be a minor change in the current technology as most likely, the organization has already allocated a laptop to each staff, but if not, the organization needs a sufficient laptop to do their work. </p>
      
      <br><br>

        <h3>How will this affect you?</h3>
        <ol type="A">
          <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>In your daily life, how will this affect you?</h4></li>
            <p>Cloud computing affects the collaboration part of daily life. It benefits the group projects for university work, giving us the ability to collaborate easily. It allows us to upload files and our work easily and efficiently to let us create the best work. It will also affect our daily lives once university is over, helping with the collaboration in the workplace, similar with the group projects in university.</p>
          <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>What will be different for you?</h4></li>
            <p>The vast difference can actually be perceived in the current situation of this COVID-19 pandemic. Although we are unable to go out of our house, we are still able to collaborate with the other team members, for example, I am writing this assignment in my house and still be able to get a live update of what the others are doing currently, and that will prove that in the future, with advancement of technology, all business processes can be done at home (Ranger, S., 2018). Also, I don't need to have a physical storage device to store my images and other files as the cloud enables us to store our assets in the cloud, in addition to that, we can access our assets without even connecting our storage device to the computer.</p>
          <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>How might this affect members of your family or your friends?</h4></li>
            <p>The usage of cloud computing can be observed in our everyday office lives by the usage of emails and data backups, everything done on a smartphone is backed up on a cloud service allowing you to access the files on multiple devices. This has many beneficial effects such as file sharing and the ability to upgrade hardware without the hassle of transferring files. Sharing between 2 different people can simply be done by providing a link with access to the required folders or documents.</p>
<br><br><br>

    <li style="font-size:30px"><h2>Data Science/Analytics</h2></li>
      <h3>What does it do?</h3>
      <ol type="A">
        <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>What is the state of the art of this new technology?</h4></li>
          <p>Currently the state of the art technology for Data Statistic/Analytics is Sisense, like cloud computing it also has many competitors, such as, Looker and Zoho Analytics. Sisense allows users to put all their “information from different sources into a unified repository, produces visual and robust analysis reports with ease and ability to easily share data, information and reports” (Sisense Reviews: Pricing & Software Features of sisense.com | FinancesOnline, 2020). It’s system allows it to “maximise 64-bit computers, multi-core CPUs and parallelization capabilities to create a very rapid and efficient system” (Sisense Reviews: Pricing & Software Features of sisense.com | FinancesOnline, 2020). The app has an In-Chip engine that allows users to ask any question with an immediate response. Sisense also has a Single Stack architecture that performs data integration to visualisation with a single BI solution with instant deployment. All the data is analyzed accurately and in real time to avoid data errors when analyzing big or small amounts of data, they do this by compiling all this data in a single place. Sisense also has the ability to be integrated with other applications using Sisense’s REST API.</p>
        <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>What can be done now?</h4></li>
          <p>Sisense and many other state of the art data statistic/analytics software/applications have pretty much done everything it can for Data Statistic/Analytics. Improvements can’t seem to come from the software of these applications, but the way users implement these to their business or lives. Business’ can use Data statistics/analytics to understand the averages and probability, this can help for “profit/loss statements, but also to figure out how to use different business operations effectively” (How Statistics And Data Analytics Can Improve Your Business, 2020). These data statistics/analytics applications can be implemented to  a business’ performance metrics, showing data of employees if they’re “pulling their weight” and check the business’ performance as a whole, showing how efficiently it's working. This also works well with the hiring process, which in turn increases “market share” (How Statistics And Data Analytics Can Improve Your Business, 2020).</p>
        <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>What is likely to be done soon (say in the next 3 years)?</h4></li>
          <p>The ability to better make decisions by utilizing data and artificial intelligence to use the data and create the best case scenario, uses of this can be observed in auto piloting cars, they use sensors that feed them with all sorts of data to be able to determine a path acceptable to the situation required. In the future this may be attached to car insurance premiums where you provide the sensor details from your vehicle so insurance companies can better visualise how you use your vehicle and provide the most custom-made policy. Every device in the future may be able to be linked together to exchange all data about itself such as location, health, weather, error messages and be able to be self-diagnosed by  artificial intelligence  to be able to inform us when the machine breaks down to be able to  schedule maintenance before it happens.</p>
        <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>What technological or other developments make this possible?</h4></li>
          <p>The ability to use Predictive analytics enable data previously collected to be able to provide a low risk decision of the potential trends in the future, mixing this with artificial intelligence that is able to decipher all this information and sperate the important parts and focus on improvements with that data. Cloud computing in distributing the large amounts of data required to provide analytics and provide backups to information gathered. Certain programs are specifically designed to interpret the massive amount of data gathered by analytics and condense them into usable information that can be focused on improving or optimizing decisions made, such programs include Amazon EMR, Apache Hive and many others. As more sensors become more accurate and the ability to record more things grows, so does the adaptability of analytics and the predictions they can create.</p>
      </ol>
<br><br>

      <h3>What is the likely impact?</h3>
        <p>Data Statistic/Analytics defines as investigation of raw data in order to make it a meaningful piece of information for the organization. This development will impact an organization's way of decision making and boosting an organization’s competitive advantage by a quicker reaction to consumer behaviour which leads to opening new opportunities to the organization and thus, competitive advantage for the business (Impact of Data Analytics in Business: A Modern Approach, 2018). The obvious change of data analytics is that the organization management and decision making style would be very dynamic as the datas will vary every second, the organization will make a lot of predictions and get deeper insight of the organization. The most affected people would be business analyst, as they are consistently improving organization’s business process, data analyst, with a various constant data coming in, they must make the report and make predictions, lastly, product manager, as they are in charge of getting the information about consumer taste and following the customer’s needs and wants. This will clearly make new job opportunities, as organizations will do anything to gain competitive advantage and thus, making new job space for data scientists and data analysts (Sandlin, 2015). There will also be a creation of jobs in the organization’s R&D team for the data statistics AI to make more accurate predictions for the upcoming future.</p>

<br><br>

      <h3>How will this affect you?</h3>
      <ol type="A">
        <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>In your daily life, how will this affect you?</h4></li>
          <p>Data Statistics/Analytics doesn’t affect us much currently, when in university not needing any of the statistics for the workload we are given. Once in the workforce it will be needed to be implemented to give employees a way to give statistics/analytics to a higher position or if we are running a business we would need these statistics/analytics to be able to see the progress of the business.Data Statistics/Analytics doesn’t affect us much currently, when in university not needing any of the statistics for the workload we are given. Once in the workforce it will be needed to be implemented to give employees a way to give statistics/analytics to a higher position or if we are running a business we would need these statistics/analytics to be able to see the progress of the business.</p>
        <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>What will be different for you?</h4></li>
          <p>For our personal lives, it would be clearly seen as what we need and what we want, organizations will react quickly as they are also striving to be the market leader, and thus, we can get our needs and wants faster in the public (Defining Data Analytics and How They Impact Everyday Life, 2016).In my personal experience, from my phone, I can see the percentages on how much time im spending on each and every application in my phone with the help of data statistics including my cell phone plan, they collect data on past usage and show how much data im spending on which application</p>
        <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>How might this affect members of your family or your friends?</h4></li>
          <p>Data analytics shape the way we interact with the digital world on a daily basis, by being able to create a unique profile of things that might interest you or people that you may know, Facebook recommended friends use mutual contacts in order to provide potential recommendations of connections that you know in order to make finding someone you may know easier. The ability of recommendations can be easily done by utilizing what others like around you, what your friends are watching might be of interest to you.</p>
  <br><br><br>

    <li style="font-size:30px"><h2>Internet of Things (IoT)</h2></li>
      <h3>What does it do?</h3>
        <ol type="A">
        <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>What is the state of the art of this new technology?</h4></li>
          <p>The Internet of Things (IoT) is getting bigger, with easier and cheaper access to the internet as well as many different devices that can be connected. Therefore, there are many states of the art of IoT. Such as devices that can help with the daily lives for instance Skybell or Ring which are focused on smart video doorbells. Through connecting a doorbell to your smartphone, you can hear and talk to visitors as well as be alerted to movement. Or TP-Link or Deako which have smart LED light switches and bulbs, enabling the user to have freedom to turn on the light or change colour from anywhere. Thus, making it simple and convenient for one's style. IoT can also be used for much larger tasks such as MyMDBand which help provide medical information about the user like medical conditions, vaccinations or medical tests, changing the landscape of storing medical information. Cujo uses IoT to create a “smart firewall” which can protect connected devices in your home from cyber attack and hackers creating a safer place.</p>
        <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>What can be done now?</h4></li>
          <p>The Internet of Things currently is a very stable system, the biggest issue to the Internet of Things is potentially how vulnerable and exposed it is to be hacked. Given that data is stored in a cloud and the ever growing number of devices using the internet, if targeted and hacked into, many important and valuable data will be exposed to the world.  This could be stopped with the creation of future AI that can detect this problems as current AI that are on offer have limits that it cannot get around due to the large amount of data base AI have to go through.</p>
        <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>What is likely to be done soon (say in the next 3 years)?</h4></li>
          <p></p>
        <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>What technological or other developments make this possible?</h4></li>
          <p></p>
        </ol>

    <br><br>

      <h3>What is the likely impact?</h3>
          <p>Due to the large growth of modern day devices integrating with internet connectivity, it’ll force organizations to redesign their data and analytical capabilities, take up new data management technologies and platforms, and create new governance policies and practices to take measures for all this data. Ted Friedman, a vice president and distinguished analyst at Gartner (IT service management company), had explained at a data & analytics summit how through 2019, ‘one third of IoT solutions will be abandoned before deployment due to lack of data management and analytics capabilities adapted for IoT’.</p>
          <p>Things that are likely to change are due to IoT are smarter homes, and wearable technology. Despite how these changes provide new products and possibilities for users, IoT will also allow for changes within the way we do business. Things such as: Inventory Management where smart devices will eventually be able to automatically track inventory, Consumer Demands and how these consumers will get used to using ‘smart devices’ which allows others to develop and meet these new demands and offers, and Remote Work as IoT becomes more integrated, more remote working opportunities will become available for tasks which had required people to be on-site to complete.</p>
          <p>People who will most likely be affected by IoT are people in hospitality, retail, manufacturing and farmers. For hospitality, hotels are already introducing a facial recognition system where they are able to recognise customers when they enter and leave. With retail, rather than visiting stores, people might soon be able to try on different outfits without leaving their homes using augmented reality or virtual reality. For manufacturers, it will help them track assets in their factories which increase their analytics functionality through installing predictive maintenance systems. Lastly, for farmers, ‘smart agriculture’ is already being implemented through the use of agriculture drones and sensors, later, potentially monitoring every plant and animal individually, assigning each with personal feeding or medical regime.</p>
          <p>As IoT is connecting millions of devices to the internet, it allows for more jobs to be created as there would be a need for more IT professionals. It is said how “by the year 2020, 250,000 IoT applications would have been developed” which would mean that there would be more opportunities for developers. Ultimately, IoT will create more jobs than it will take away.</p>

    <br><br>
      
      <h3>In your daily life, how will this affect you? In your daily life, how will this affect you? What will be different for you? How might this affect members of your family or your friends?</h3>
      <ol type="A">
        <li style="font-size:20px">
          <p>The Internet of Things (IoT) is commonly used in our daily life. The connection between our devices to the internet is already used by many people. IoT expands the use of technologies at home with smart home systems that allow users to control aspects of their home with a command from their phone. These aspects include controlling the lighting and temperature of a household. IoT has also allowed us to use smart appliances such as fridges that can control the temperature of food items in different sections of a fridge. In my daily life, IoT is greatly used at home. My phone and smart home devices are connected to the internet which allows me to control the light switches from my phone. I also use smart wearables such as Fitbit, which connects via Bluetooth to my phone. The collation of my heart rate and steps are then transmitted via the internet so it is uploaded to my phone. IoT connects us to our devices where technology is now commonly used. IoT is also commonly used for mobile payments. IoT connects phones to their banks allowing us to use mobile payments to pay for goods and services. IoT also allows banks to use applications that we can control to view our money balances and saving accounts. IoT affects my family and friends with the use of applications such as WeChat or Messenger. IoT is being used by these applications where our devices would connect to the internet and transmit data to these applications allowing my family and friends to communicate to each other over the internet via texting or video calls. IoT is used by our parents making it easy for them to connect devices to save and share photos on the internet. </p>
        </li>
        </ol>
<br><br><br>

    <li style="font-size:30px"><h2>Cybersecurity</h2></li>
      <h3>What does it do?</h3>
      <ol type="A">
        <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>What is the state of the art of this new technology?</h4></li>
          <p>Cybersecurity is a very comparative area, therefore there is no one single company with state of the art of cybersecurity but instead there are many. Securiti.AI provides AI-powered PrivacyOps solutions for today's privacy regulations “ (Top 10 Most Innovative Cybersecurity Companies After RSA 2020, 2020) thus easing the workload and making information hard to access for attackers. Similarly ImmuniWeb aims to use artificial intelligence to aim for “reduce complexity and costs” for companies (Top 10 Most Innovative Cybersecurity Companies After RSA 2020, 2020). Which can allow them to accelerate monitoring among many other things to help combat cyber attackers. Qulays uses an “all in one cloud based app” (Top 10 Most Innovative Cybersecurity Companies After RSA 2020, 2020) which can automate many of the difficult tasks such as automating the vulnerability management cycle across endpoints, cloud and more. It can also help detect and protect IT assets, thus saving time and convenience which could be used for other tasks and be able to respond to other threats or attacks.  </p>
        <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>What can be done now?</h4></li>
          <p>What can be done now to cybersecurity is to make it more difficult to infiltrate from cyber attackers although it is easier said than done as there are many cybersecurity threats. For example, malware attacks, password decryption, hacking. However, there are ways to improve cybersecurity such as the use of artificial intelligence, as with the improvement in technology cyber criminals are using, AI can detect these suspicious movements and identify them. Thus, protecting and securing the important information as AI can do more than one person. Like AI, the improvement automation can reduce the workload for the cybersecurity companies as it can also help block and detect attacks.</p>
        <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>What is likely to be done soon (say in the next 3 years)?</h4></li>
          <p></p>
        <li style="font-size:20px"><h4>What technological or other developments make this possible?</h4></li>
          <p></p>
      </ol>
    <br><br>

      <h3>What is the likely impact?</h3>
        <p></p>

    <br><br>

      <h3>In your daily life, how will this affect you? What will be different for you? How might this affect members of your family or your friends?</h3>
      <ol type="A">
        <li style="font-size:20px">
          <p>Cybersecurity is important in our daily life. Cyber security protects our information from being spread. Financial information and personal information can be stored on the internet making cybersecurity an important measure. The simple use of cybersecurity would be setting a protection for our devices with the use of passwords, passcodes or biometrics scanning. Security patches and software updates are provided by manufacturers to keep us safe from any threats or malicious attacks. We live in a time where security is a measure that manufacturers take when designing our devices, with programs that allow our biometrics to unlock our devices. Cybersecurity allows us to download files from the internet safely. When downloading from the internet, a security measure would scan the file to detect any virus or malware that could be contained in that file. Preventing hackers or organisations from stealing our data. Many services that we use are now providing 2-step verifications logins. This toggles the users to sign in twice to gain access to an account, by sending codes that can only be found in designated locations. If a hacker were to gain access to a user’s username and password as this cybersecurity measure would prevent them from accessing your account as they do not have access to the designated location. Cybersecurity is commonly used with our family and friends as they would also follow the same measures of setting passwords and using biometric scanners to protect their information.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
