  <br><br><br>
  <h1>Project Ideas</h1>
  <h2>Introduction</h2>
  <p>Telkom+ is just a simple mini computer that uses Raspberry Pi as the "MiddleMan" for the wall power socket to the electrical appliance to make it automated. This product of Telkom+ will then be connected to the home wifi to obtain the static IP address of the Raspberry Pi and so the wifi signal can control the Raspberry Pi to kill the power or reconnect the power to the electrical appliance. </p>
    <p>Next, the phone application is created using the python programming language, that will be compatible with all phone OS, whether it is iOS or Android. First, when you tap on the application, a username and password is requested or simply the user can turn the FaceID that iOS has or the user fingerprint. After the credentials are verified by the app, the home screen will appear. The home screen consists of all personalised electrical appliances, where the user can put which electrical appliance in which side of the phone screen, for example, I want to put the home heater on top of the screen and the garage door on the bottom. After the user selects which appliance he / she wants to control, the screen will then go to the next page with it showing whether it is either open / closed or on / off. </p>
    <p>After this, the user can then see the state of the appliance and can do further actions such as locking the front door, watching the live view of the CCTV or turning off the stove.</p>
  
